HEADWORD: Skinbound
<hw>Skin"bound`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having the skin
adhering closely and rigidly to the flesh; hidebound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Skinbound disease</b></col>. <fld>(Med.)</fld> <cd>See
